OL,6,FA large backlog of unprocessed claims
OL,7,Fbuilt up between 2018 and 2022,
OL,8,Falthough it started to fall in 2023 (a
OL,9,Fdrop of 28 per cent after 12 years of
OL,10,Fgrowth.)
OL,12,FAn extra 1,000 staff will be recruited
OL,13,Fto process claims and temporary courts
OL,14,Fset up to hear legal challenges
OL,15,Fquickly.
OL,17,FMany questions remain unanswered. For
OL,18,Fexample, it's unclear what the plan is
OL,19,Ffor illegal migrants whose claims are
OL,20,Frejected as they can't be sent home to
OL,21,Fcountries like Iran or Afghanistan.
